(firstQuint)Study of Operative Versus Non-operative Treatment of ER-stress Positive Ankle Fractures.

 Prospective randomized controlled comparative study of non-operative vs operative treatment of ER-stress positive unimalleolar ankle fractures.

 The ER-stress test is performed by consultant trauma orthopedic surgeon or a trauma resident with trauma service done.

 Medial clear space opening of 5mm or more was considered a positive ER stress test.

 Those patients were randomized either non-operative or operative treatment by opening the sealed envelope.

